transylvanian archaeological project home this forum is archived home this forum is archived transylvanian archaeological project key pages projects the transylvanian archaeological project trap is a collaborative endeavor between the national museum of transylvanian history cluj romania the universities of aarhus denmark umea sweden gothenburg sweden and stanford usa and the raa sweden building on preliminary fieldwork that was carried out by a team under the direction of roger engelmark in 2004 the project is set to commence during the summer of 2005 it will explore a small region of transylvania around the huge bronze age hoards of uioara de sus and spalnaca i ii through survey and focused excavations in an effort to develop an understanding of the dynamics of settlement and land use through time current announcements see project members todo and meetings for more information hints on getting started forum home site home find pages site home transylvanian archaeological project home
